holdings.text: The right of pre-emption is not a right to the thing sold but a right to the offer of a thing about to be sold. This right is called the primary or inherent right.

anchor.surface_text: To summarize  1  The right of pre-emption is number a right to the thing sold but a right to the offer of a thing about to be sold.  i   1885  I.L. R. 7 All. 775, 809.  2   1930  I.L.R. 11 Lah. 258, 273. This right is called the primary or inherent right.

holdings.reasoning_summary: Summarizing precedents like Dhani Nath and Gobind Dayal defining primary right as offer before sale.

holdings.text: The pre-emptor has a secondary right or a remedial right to follow the thing sold. It is a right of substitution but not of re-purchase, i.e., the pre-emptor takes the entire bargain and steps into the shoes of the original vendee.

anchor.surface_text: 2  The pre-emptor has a secondary right or a remedial right to follow the thing sold.  3  It is a right of substitution but number of re-purchase, i. e., the pre-emptor takes the entire bargain and steps into the shoes of the original vendee.
